cs.DC, cs.PL, cs.AR, cs.SE, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper discusses a framework for heterogeneous clusters and offloading computations to acceleration devices. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper introduces a new programming framework. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of unconventional compute cores such as FPGAs/GPUs/APUs/DSPs. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is relevant as the paper discusses the integration of the new framework into the standard Spark framework. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses new kernel function types and modified Spark transformations and actions.
